Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with online networks and their topology estimation via sampling techniques. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the paper discusses measurement strategies for efficient estimation of local graph properties. 
- cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) is another possible category as the paper focuses on social networks and their analysis. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the development of estimators for design-based inference. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper applies the methodology to a sample of Facebook users and shares the resulting data on a website.
